  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nRight now, we create a `users` module for each `chat_content`, ie each Channel.\r\nIt makes sense for personal chats (group, 1-1, public), but for communities, it creates a lot of duplication of data in memory.\r\n\r\nDo note however, having an individual list of members for community private channels will be needed in the future.\r\nWith the new Permissions, some channels will only accept users with certain conditions, so **those** particular channels will need a per chat users module.\r\n\r\nStill, most communities and most channels in a community will be \"normal\" and share the exact same members, so we can easily do a performance and memory improvement here.\r\n\r\nIt's just not straightforward, because we'd need to maybe share a reference to the main users module to the different chat ones, so as not to create a brand new user module each time.\r\n\r\nTo the person working on it, please share ideas and designs before working on it so some of us can look at them and see if they are feasible.",
