    "body": "So right now I see 2 solutions:\r\n\r\n1. Make the user module shared between all the channels in the community (as I understood, we can reach it in min via new() + ref). In this case, the user's module will be kept on the heap, not the stack. \r\nCons: Using a heap always has a risk of crashes\r\n\r\n2. Community channels can contain or not contain a users module and the users module should live in the community channel too (if it has chats without users). \r\n- If the community channel does not have a users module - a community users module is used\r\n- If the community channel has a users module - UI is using a chat users module, if not - channel users module (for community  private channels)\r\n\r\nCurrent qml code for detecting if we should display the member's list:\r\nqml code\r\n```\r\nusersModel: {\r\n                let chatContentModule = root.rootStore.currentChatContentModule()\r\n                if (!chatContentModule || !chatContentModule.usersModule) {\r\n                    // New communities have no chats, so no chatContentModule\r\n                    return null\r\n                }\r\n                return chatContentModule.usersModule.model\r\n            }\r\n```\r\n",
