    "body": "Adding the logic of choosing modules in qml seems to be wrong for me. We should do this in nim code.\r\nI checked briefly the code and it seems that:\r\n- in main module for each channel group we create chat_section_module, that means that every community has its own chat_section_module\r\n- every chat_section_module has some submodules (channels) and for every submodule chat_section_module creates chat_content_module\r\n- every chat_content module creates users_module\r\n- users module is exposed to qml via QProperty by chat_content view (channel).\r\n\r\nIt means that chat_section_module (community) should contains its own 1 instance of users_module which should be passed down to submodules (channels). In case of very specific channels we can create more users modules.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/61889657/213125419-f11d32d7-27e9-430a-a689-57315187c47a.png)\r\n",
